track_notes: Loop combining the Pinnacle Mtn Trail, the Ridge Trail and the Table Rock Trail. Distance is equivalent to an out-and-back on the Pinncale Mtn Trail, but this provides some change of scenery. I would recommend hiking the loop counter-clockwise, starting on the Table Rock Trail due to the number of steps on the Table Rock Trail. Hiking to W4C/US-006 - Table Rock from would add an additional 2.3 miles to the hike.

11 mile loop hike with 3800 EG and 3700 EL.  Mileage includes 0.7 mile roundtrip to the overlook past the Table Rock (W4C/US-006) summit.  Table Rock summit at 3.25 miles and Pinnacle Mtn summit at 6.9 miles.
track_title: W4C US-006 - Table Rock  US-002 - Pinnacle Mtn Loop

track_notes: 5 mile hike with 2500 EG.  Parking for a couple of vehicles at the end of the gated Alewine Rd access just off of Hwy 11 (35.003453, -82.740232).  Follow Alewine Rd trail 0.8 miles to the Palmetto Trail.  Take a left on the Palmetto Trail for around 0.7 miles, then take a sharp right onto another forest road which meets back up with the Palmetto Trail in a mile.  Turn right and follow the Palmetto Trail for another 0.2 miles before taking a right on Long Ridge Rd. Long Ridge Rd will meet up with the Foothills Trail in another 1.1 miles, take a right and follow the Foothills Trail past Drawbar Cliffs another 1.1 miles before turning left on the Pinnacle Mtn trail for the final steep climb.
track_title: W4C US-002 - Pinnacle Mtn via Long Ridge-Alewine Rd
